@ROME|King Bryan-Titan Analytics bringing it here to avoid chatting in FR.

Toolkits require 0 crew to install, and give 14 LP.

At a t4 base, it's about 16.5m/day burned, for a total of 230m LP. For a single base. No crew required.

@Narr_nEoN - ⁠😎┃foundation-room⁠

It's a pretty difficult problem to solve but I haven't stopped thinking about how to "combat" this behavior. Sadly limiting based on users (wallets) is pretty easy to work around since wallets are free and can be easily scripted. It does appear that they're shotgunning accept_rental to snag them when they become available.

This will become even easier once the SDK is released and as such is the top of my list. One answer is to make it available to everyone (but that sort of fights fire with fire). Another answer is to increase the supply of fleets on the market (but that requires users to use the rental system). Another answer is to implement some sort of crowdbased market valuation tool. Since a lot of people are annoyed at these bots getting the best deals. If all the deals were "equal" the bots will be paying the same as everyone else. At which point, if it still happens it tells me that there's more demand than supply at hand as well.

